  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide a range of Quantity Surveying duties from project inception through to completion</li>\n  <li>Preparation of pre-contract cost estimates, cost plans, budgetary study and project cash-flow</li>\n  <li>Measurement (taking off quantities) for all structural and architectural elements</li>\n  <li>Preparation of tender and contract documentation</li>\n  <li>Tendering process and tender evaluation</li>\n  <li>Post-contract administration and management such as valuation of progress payment, review of variation request order, variation assessment.</li>\n  <li>Finalization of project final accounts</li>\n  <li>Attendance at project and site meeting</li>\n  <li>Proper guidance and mentorship will be provided</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in Building, Quantity Surveying or equivalent from recognized universities</li>\n  <li>Minimum of 2 years of QS relevant working experience </li>\n  <li>Good technical knowledge for measurement, cost estimating and construction technology</li>\n  <li>Understand and familiar with professional practice and contract administration processes</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal, communication and negotiation skills</li>\n  <li>Able to work as a team player and multi-task on few on-going projects/ assignments</li>\n  <li>Resourceful, independent, responsible and able to work in a fast paced environment</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
